1. cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) - The paper focuses on creating modular inflatable actuators as building blocks for prototyping room-scale shape-changing interfaces, which is a key area of research in HCI.
2. cs.RO (Robotics) - The use of inflatable actuators for shape-changing interfaces has applications in robotics, particularly in soft robotics.
3. cs.ME (Mechanical Engineering) - The paper discusses the design and implementation of inflatable actuators, which is a topic of interest in mechanical engineering.
4. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The control of the inflatable actuators using air pressure is a topic of interest in systems and control.
5. cs.ET (Emerging Technologies) - The use of modular inflatable actuators as building blocks for prototyping room-scale shape-changing interfaces is an emerging technology with potential applications in various fields.
